One of the best things in horse racing over the past 40 years has been a man called Mick Goss. The phrase “force of nature” has been used for lesser mortals than the boss of Summerhill Stud, but it’s a description that suits him perfectly. Champion breeder Goss – with his enviable optimism, ambition and energy – seemed like an ever-present force for good in racing. As long as Mick was around, we’d all be OK. That’s no longer the case. On Tuesday came shock news that Goss’s Summerhill Stud near Mooi River is selling the bulk of its bloodstock...